<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="163" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2024]" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1493,1519]" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Aswaj &amp; Anoop &amp; Priyadarsanan, 2021" authorityName="Aswaj &amp; Anoop &amp; Priyadarsanan" authorityYear="2021" box="[332,538,1494,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmecina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bawai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[332,538,1494,1520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">Myrmecina bawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[549,642,1494,1520]" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[549,642,1494,1520]" pageId="3" pageNumber="163" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is unique in the following combination of characters: 1) small eyes (
<quantity box="[159,329,1530,1557]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="163" unit="mm" value="0.045" valueMax="0.05" valueMin="0.04">0.04–0.05 mm</quantity>
); 2) anterolateral corners of the median portion of clypeus with dentiform process; 3) absence of tooth like process on the middle anterior clypeal margin; 4) head and mesosoma with distinct rugae, the interspaces between rugae densely punctate; 5) presence of anterior pair of denticles on propodeal dorsum; 6) first gastral tergum punctulate anteriorly, coarsely reticulate medially; 7) yellow coloured body with a dark tinge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="165" pageId="3" pageNumber="163" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2024]" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,421,1673,1700]" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">Description. Head.</emphasis>
In full face view, subrectangular with strongly concave occipital margin and weakly convex posterolateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[402,495,1710,1736]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,248,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[195,1391,525,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-175@4.[195,1391,525,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Myrmecina bawai sp. nov. worker, holotype; A) Head in full face view; B) Body in dorsal view; C) Body in profile view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982574/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">Fig. 2 A</figureCitation>
). Masticatory margin of mandible with large apical tooth followed by small preapical tooth, robust third tooth, five denticles and a blunt basal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[863,960,1746,1772]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1318,1342]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,182,1293]" captionTargetId="figure-27@5.[151,1435,181,1294]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Myrmecina bawai sp. nov. worker, holotype; A) Clypeus and mandibles; B) Mesosoma in dorsal view; C) Denticle on propodeal dorsum, propodeal spine, petiole and postpetiole in profile view; D) First gastral tergum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982576/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">Fig. 3 A</figureCitation>
). Clypeus with distinctly convex posterior margin, anterior margin nearly straight, anterolateral corners of the median portion of the clypeus with dentiform process (
<figureCitation box="[250,349,1818,1844]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,248,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[195,1391,525,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-175@4.[195,1391,525,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Myrmecina bawai sp. nov. worker, holotype; A) Head in full face view; B) Body in dorsal view; C) Body in profile view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982574/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">Figs 2 A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[360,404,1818,1844]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1318,1342]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,182,1293]" captionTargetId="figure-27@5.[151,1435,181,1294]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Myrmecina bawai sp. nov. worker, holotype; A) Clypeus and mandibles; B) Mesosoma in dorsal view; C) Denticle on propodeal dorsum, propodeal spine, petiole and postpetiole in profile view; D) First gastral tergum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982576/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">3 A</figureCitation>
). Antennae 12 segmented with three segmented club; antennal segment II pear-shaped; each segment of III–IX slightly shorter than broad; apical segment (XII) distinctly longer than segments X and XI combined. Scape almost reaching posterolateral corner of head. Eyes very small, 
<quantity box="[1000,1098,1890,1917]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="163" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
in diameter, located anteriorly at the lateral margin of head at a distance of 
<quantity box="[648,748,1926,1952]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="163" unit="mm" value="0.27">0.27 mm</quantity>
from the point of mandibular insertion (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1296,1926,1952]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,248,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[195,1391,525,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-175@4.[195,1391,525,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Myrmecina bawai sp. nov. worker, holotype; A) Head in full face view; B) Body in dorsal view; C) Body in profile view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982574/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">Fig. 2 A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1133,2024]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="164" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1962,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="163">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
In profile view, dorsal outline weakly convex, sloping backward; anterior ventrolateral corner of pronotum forming a very short tooth like process; mesonotum completely fused with pronotum; mesometapleural suture is feebly visible through the cuticle. Propodeal dorsum weakly demarcated anteriorly; metanotal groove indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[249,344,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,248,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[195,1391,525,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-175@4.[195,1391,525,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Myrmecina bawai sp. nov. worker, holotype; A) Head in full face view; B) Body in dorsal view; C) Body in profile view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982574/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="164">Fig. 2 B</figureCitation>
). In profile view, propodeal dorsum has a small denticle on anterior part; propodeal spines longer than broad at base, curved up apically; propodeal declivity steep and strongly concave (
<figureCitation box="[1131,1230,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,248,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[195,1391,525,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-175@4.[195,1391,525,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Myrmecina bawai sp. nov. worker, holotype; A) Head in full face view; B) Body in dorsal view; C) Body in profile view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982574/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="164">Figs 2 C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1241,1284,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1318,1342]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,182,1293]" captionTargetId="figure-27@5.[151,1435,181,1294]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Myrmecina bawai sp. nov. worker, holotype; A) Clypeus and mandibles; B) Mesosoma in dorsal view; C) Denticle on propodeal dorsum, propodeal spine, petiole and postpetiole in profile view; D) First gastral tergum in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982576/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="164">3 C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="164">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,259,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="164">Metasoma.</emphasis>
In dorsal view, petiole longer than broad, almost parallel sides; postpetiole slightly broader than petiole, broader than long, semicircular, weakly concave anterior margin and distinctly convex posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[160,257,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,248,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[195,1391,525,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-175@4.[195,1391,525,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Myrmecina bawai sp. nov. worker, holotype; A) Head in full face view; B) Body in dorsal view; C) Body in profile view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982574/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="164">Fig. 2 B</figureCitation>
). In profile view, petiole almost as long as high (excluding subpetiolar process); petiolar dorsal surface weakly concave; anterior slope nearly straight; narrow subpetiolar process with relatively broad anterior tip; postpetiole slightly elevated than petiole, almost as long as high (excluding sternopostpetiolar process); sternopostpetiolar process well developed, roundly convex ventral outline, straight anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1189,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,248,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[195,1391,525,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-175@4.[195,1391,525,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Myrmecina bawai sp. nov. worker, holotype; A) Head in full face view; B) Body in dorsal view; C) Body in profile view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982574/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="164">Figs 2 C</figureCitation>
